						<summary>

						<p>Same pillar, third face.</p>						

						<p>Seems to state that Bētana, the lord of the Chōḍas, obtained Nannūru on the banks of the Guṇḍi. Also praises Komma of Kāśyapa-<hi rend="italic">gōtra</hi> and the lord of Nannūru.</p>						

